h1. f:widget

h2. Description

_f:widget_ renders an appropriate widget for a property, for example an @<input type="text">@ element for a _String_ property or a @<select>@ for an enum.

{note}
Using _f:widget_ directly will only be necessary for very specialized cases, usually it will be invoked via _f:field_.
{note}

h2. Attributes

_f:widget_ accepts exactly the same attributes as the _f:[field|Tags]_ tag (except for _wrapper_ and _templates_ attributes).